# Pelican UI â€” Styling Conventions


## General Rules
- For layouting, use Ant Design's grid layout components like `<Row>`, `<Col>`, `Flex`.
- Avoid inline styles.
- Avoid adding too much of css code.
- Use CSS modules. Each feature mapped to a certain route to have single .module.scss file.
- Use bootstrap ultility css classes instead of adding inline css or creating new classes.

### File naming conventions
- Styles: `PascalCase.module.scss` (or existing feature SCSS file when already established)

## CSS Modules (`.module.scss`)
- Every component with custom styles MUST use a co-located `.module.scss` file:

```tsx
import styles from './FeatureName.module.scss'

const Feature = () => (
  <div className={styles.container}>
    <h1 className={styles.title}>Title</h1>
  </div>
)
```
- Import as `styles`: `import styles from './Component.module.scss'`
- Use camelCase for class names in SCSS: `.contentWrapper`, `.glossaryCard`, `.headerTitle`
- Apply via `className={styles.className}`
- Combine with Bootstrap utilities using template literals: `` className={`fw-bold ps-2 ${styles.myClass}`} ``
- Use BEM naming convention for class names in SCSS files, e.g. `.card`, `.card__header`, `.card__body`, `.card--active`
- Avoid defining values in `px`; prefer relative units like `rem` for better scalability and accessibility

## SCSS Conventions

- Use nesting for component-scoped styles
- Leverage shared variables from `src/assets/styles/variables.scss`
- Use mixins from `src/assets/styles/mixins.scss` where applicable
- Ant Design theme overrides go in `src/assets/styles/core.scss`, not in module files
- Any common styles that are shared across multiple components should be placed in `src/assets/styles/core.scss` and imported into the relevant module files
- Use `@use` to import shared styles and variables into module SCSS files:
- Use scss related functions and features (e.g. variables, mixins, nesting, extends) to keep styles organized and maintainable, but avoid over-nesting which can lead to specificity issues.

```scss
@use 'src/assets/styles/variables' as vars;
```

## Bootstrap utilities
- The project uses Bootstrap 5 utility classes alongside CSS modules
- Common utilities: `fw-bold`, `text-primary`, `text-white`, `d-inline-block`, `float-start`, `ps-*`, `pe-*`, `mb-*`, `mt-*`, `m-0`, `p-0`, `col-md-*`, `row`, `text-break`, `text-capitalize`, `text-end`, `bg-primary`, `cursor-pointer`
- Spacing: `m-3`, `p-0`, `mt-5`, `me-3`, `mb-2`
- Grid: `col-md-12`, `row`
- Cards: `card`, `card-body`
- Display: `d-flex`, `d-none`

### Class name composition
- Use template literals for combining static classes with module classes

```tsx
<div className={`m-3 ${styles.container}`} />
```


## Anti-patterns (Do NOT)

- No inline styles (`style={{...}}`) â€” use CSS Modules or Bootstrap utility clases
- No Tailwind CSS
- No styled-components or CSS-in-JS
- No global class names in `.module.scss` files (they are auto-scoped)
- No new plain `.css` files â€” always use `.module.scss`
- Style files are always co-located with their `.tsx` component (not `.jsx`)
- No new colors to be defined in SCSS files; use existing variables from `variables.scss` or add new ones there if needed
